This paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning for congestion control in datacenter networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also focuses on the use of deep reinforcement learning algorithms, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of using reinforcement learning in a practical setting, which could fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or cryptography and security (cs.CR).
